HEADWORD: Latescent
<hw>La*tes"cent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>latescens</ets>, <ets>-entis</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>latescere</ets>
to be concealed, fr. <ets>latere</ets> to be hid.]</ety> <def>Slightly
withdrawn from view or knowledge; <as>as, a <ex>latescent</ex>
meaning</as>.</def> <rj><au>Sir W. Hamilton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

